COMPONENT NAME: LKM JMS to SQL
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description : - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from a JMS compliant Message Oriented Middleware (MOM) to any ISO-92 compliant target database. - This module uses ODI Agent to read selected data from the source MOM and write the result in the target temporary table created dynamically.
Restrictions: - The message format must be either delimited or fixed length. - Each message is a database record.
Commit the message consumption on the Router (JMS)
Set this option to false if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
NOT USED for consumption. This option is described only for JMS compatibility.

Maximum number of messages retrieved [0 .. 4 000 000 000]. 0: All messages are retrieved.
Set the Session Durability. D: Session is durable. Indicates that the subscriber definition remains on the router after disconnection.

Time to wait in milliseconds for the first message [0 (infinite wait) to 4,000,000,000 (maximum wait)].
If MESSAGETIMEOUT is equal to 0, then there is no timeout.
MESSAGETIMEOUT and MESSAGEMAXNUMBER cannot be both equal to zero.
If MESSAGETIMEOUT=0 and MESSAGEMAXNUMBER=0, then MESSAGETIMEOUT takes the value 1.
Warning!: An interface may retrieve no messages if this timeout value is too small.

Time to wait for each subsequent message in milliseconds [0 (infinite wait) to 4,000,000,000 (maximum wait)]. The default value is 5000.
'''Warning!''': An interface may retrieve only a subset of the messages available in the topic or the queue if this value is too small.
